  <!-- §11 How to Use -->
  <section class="how-to-use">
    <h2>How to Use Your LAGRATY Knitted Weighted Blanket for Best Results</h2>
    <ol class="step-list">
      <li>
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <div class="step-text">
          <strong>Layer it correctly.</strong> Use the weighted blanket as a top layer, on top of your regular sheets and light comforter (if you use one). This maximizes the pressure-on-skin effect. Don't use it as your only blanket in winter—you'll get cold. Pair it with a duvet underneath for warmth and a knit blanket on top for weight.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <div class="step-text">
          <strong>Give it 2–3 weeks to work.</strong> Your nervous system needs time to adapt to the new pressure sensation. Night one might feel weird. By day 14–21, your body recognizes the blanket as a safety signal, and sleep will deepen. Don't judge effectiveness after one night.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <div class="step-text">
          <strong>Wash in cold water, lay flat to dry.</strong> Machine wash on gentle cycle with cold water (hot water can damage the knit). Don't use bleach or fabric softener. Lay flat to dry; don't throw it in the dryer, which will shrink the yarn. Takes 24–48 hours to dry completely.
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

