        <div class="bar-score">62</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Key finding:</strong> The knitted blanket excels at breathability, silence, and aesthetics. It felt noticeably cooler than bead-filled models and never made noise when we shifted positions. Durability is solid—after 30 washes, zero pilling or deterioration. The price-to-performance ratio is the weak point: you're paying 2–3x more for features (no beads, knit) that matter if you prioritize comfort and design, but not if you're chasing pure therapeutic pressure.</p>
  </section>

