    <div class="pros">
      <h3>Pros</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Silent operation:</strong> Zero crunching. Knitted construction absorbs movement noise.</li>
        <li><strong>Even weight distribution:</strong> No bead migration means consistent pressure all night.</li>
        <li><strong>Breathable & cool:</strong> Chunky knit lets air flow through; doesn't trap heat like dense fabrics.</li>
        <li><strong>Machine washable:</strong> Cold water wash, lay flat to dry. No special care.</li>
        <li><strong>Pet-safe:</strong> No loose beads to ingest if seams fail or pet chews it.</li>
        <li><strong>Beautiful aesthetic:</strong> Looks like designer home decor, not a medical device.</li>
        <li><strong>Consistent quality:</strong> LAGRATY's knit construction is tight and even. No loose threads.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cons">
      <h3>Cons</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Expensive:</strong> $290 is steep for a 7lbs blanket. Bead models are $80–140.</li>
        <li><strong>Too light for heavier adults:</strong> If you weigh over 200 lbs, 7 lbs will feel like a regular blanket, not therapeutic.</li>
        <li><strong>Limited pressure intensity:</strong> Knitted construction is gentler than bead-filled. If you need a "weighted vest" feeling, this won't deliver.</li>
        <li><strong>Takes 2–3 weeks to feel effects:</strong> Not an instant sleep improvement. Your nervous system needs adaptation time.</li>
        <li><strong>Drying time:</strong> Lay-flat drying takes 24–48 hours. Can't speed it up in the dryer.</li>
        <li><strong>Not ideal for extreme climates:</strong> Still warm in very hot summers. Won't provide enough warmth in freezing climates without a duvet underneath.</li>
        <li><strong>Size limited:</strong> Only available in 50" × 60" (twin/throw size). No queen or king options.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
