    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Is 7 lbs heavy enough for a weighted blanket?</h3>
      <p>Yes, if you weigh 80–160 lbs. The rule of thumb is 10% of your body weight. At 7 lbs, this blanket targets lighter adults and teenagers. If you weigh over 200 lbs, 7 lbs will feel like a regular throw blanket. You'd need 15+ lbs for therapeutic effect.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Why is this so much more expensive than bead-filled blankets?</h3>
      <p>Knitted construction is labor-intensive. Each blanket is woven with yarn weight distributed evenly throughout—no bulk bead suppliers or cheap filling. It's a small-batch manufacturing model. You're also paying for the design innovation: breathability, silence, and washability are worth the premium if those features matter to you.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can you machine wash this blanket?</h3>
      <p>Yes. Cold water, gentle cycle, no bleach, no softener. Lay flat to dry (don't use the dryer). Drying takes 24–48 hours. We tested it through 30 wash cycles with zero pilling or deterioration. It holds up extremely well.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What if my pet chews through it?</h3>
      <p>No glass beads will spill out. The yarn weight is woven into the entire blanket, so there's nothing to ingest. This is a huge advantage over bead-filled models, where seam failure means loose beads. Still, supervise pets around any blanket to prevent damage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Will this make me sleep better immediately?</h3>
      <p>Unlikely on night one. Your nervous system needs 2–3 weeks to recognize the pressure as a safety signal. Deep pressure works through learned association. By week 3, you'll notice you fall asleep faster and wake less. Patience is required.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How does this compare to a regular throw blanket?</h3>
      <p>A regular throw is just warmth and coziness. This weighted blanket provides deep pressure stimulation, which activates your parasympathetic nervous system (the "rest and digest" mode). If you just want something warm and soft, save your money on a regular throw. If you have anxiety or restlessness, weighted pressure is different and better.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can I use this in summer?</h3>
      <p>Yes, better than bead-filled models. The knit is breathable and won't trap heat like dense fabrics. That said, you're still putting 7 lbs on top of yourself. If your bedroom is over 75°F, pair it with lightweight cotton sheets underneath. Hot sleepers should consider a lighter weight (5 lbs) or skip to summer—use it April–October, not July.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What's the return policy?</h3>
      <p>Check Shopify's customer return policy (typically 30 days). Most weighted blankets have return windows because some people find them uncomfortable. If it doesn't work for you after 2 weeks, you should be able to return it. Don't judge too early.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What's the actual size of this blanket?</h3>
      <p>The LAGRATY Knitted Weighted Blanket measures 50" x 60" — suitable for one person on a full-size bed or two people on a queen. It's not large enough to completely cover a queen mattress for two people; it's designed for single-person or light couples use. Measure your bed before ordering.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Does this blanket have a strong smell or odor when new?</h3>
      <p>Most knitted weighted blankets have minimal odor upon arrival, especially compared to bead-filled models. If there's any smell, it typically fades after one wash and 24 hours of airing out. Air dry flat or machine wash on gentle cycle — both work.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can I use a weighted blanket if I have back pain or injuries?</h3>
      <p>Deep pressure can help some people with back pain by promoting relaxation. However, it can aggravate others — it depends on the cause of your pain. If you have serious back issues, consult your doctor before using. Lighter weights (5 lbs) are safer than 7+ lbs if you have concerns.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

